This file lists a summary of the new features introduced in GPS. For more
details, please see the documentation.

New features in GPS 2.0.0

- Support for custom Version Control Systems through XML files

- Documentation is now provided in PDF format (which replaces PS format)

- D316-008 Improved startup time with network drives

- Less memory used to compute the cross-references (e.g find all references)

- Improved rendering of fonts under Linux and Solaris 8 (using libXft)

- Python interpreter
  Under Linux, Solaris and Windows, GPS now comes with an integrated python
  interpreter, giving the ability to write powerful GPS extensions.

- Python files recognized by source and project editors.

- Speed up in block folding

- Support for casing exceptions for case insensitive languages

- Support for global ChangeLog file. This file can be used to record
  revision history, GPS will extract from this file the revision history for a
  file to commit, if present.

- Ability to enter a revision log when adding/removing files from the VCS

- Display of current function name into the status bar

- New menu Edit->Insert File... to insert the contents of a file in the current
  editor.

- The locations view can be sorted by category
  So that you can e.g. separate error messages from warnings in build output

- The locations view displays the total number of items belonging to each
  category and sub-category.

- Custom languages can specify a regular expression for recognizing comments

- D204-015 Separator between switches and arguments can be specified in the
  XML files

- C725-012 If you exit GPS while tasks are running in the background, a window
  will display these running tasks and ask for confirmation.

- Customization files can create submenus in contextual menus

- Ability to change the default foreground and background colors in the editors
  through the preferences dialog

- Callgraph displays clickable references location

- CB13-017 Improved handling of C++ classes in the Entity Browser

- CB14-004 New menu Make->All
  GPS now provides via the menus 'Make->Compile all sources' and 'Make->All'
  the ability to either compile all files from the project, or to compile
  and link all main units in a given project.

- Speed Column
  This column appears on the left of the editors to show an overview of the
  lines highlighted in the file, for example to show the current debugger
  location, or compilation errors.

- CB13-012 Improved search result display
  When searching in an editor, if a search result is off the screen, scrolling
  will ensure that some context is visible before and after the search result.

- BC08-007 Faster loading and rendering of big files

- Support for hooks, including from scripting languages

- Support for themes (predefined set of colors, keys, ...)

- Ability to reformat text when automatic indentation is disabled
  The key used to indent the current line/selection is now active even
  when automatic indentation is disabled.

- Improved speed and responsiveness of automated text formatting

- Improved interface for the project wizard
  The source directory selector now supports multiple selections.

- Selection automatically put in the search entry
  If there is an active selection, this selection will be used as the default
  pattern when doing a new search

- Improvements in handling of key bindings in floating windows

